snippet.title: Porsche Museum showcases company's great history
snippet.description: Road Trip 2011: From Professor Porsche's earliest designs for his first employers to his own company's million-dollar creations, the modern masterpiece of showmanship in Stuttgart-Zuffenhausen, Germany is worth any car fan's time.

snippet.title: Making and breaking codes at the NSA museum
snippet.description: Road Trip 2010: CNET reporter Daniel Terdiman stops in on the National Cryptologic Museum and sees a bit of the history of codes and codebreaking.

snippet.title: Mini Museum puts skulls, gold, London Bridge in your pocket
snippet.description: Indiana Jones would approve of the Mini Museum. Fragments of dinosaur bones, meteorites, famous landmarks, and other fascinating things are displayed in resin, and could be yours via Kickstarter.

snippet.title: At the BMW Museum, 82 years of carmaking shines
snippet.description: Road Trip 2011: Located adjacent to BMW headquarters and the uber-modern BMW Welt, this homage to eight-plus decades of car-making is a must-see for any real fan of the famous Germany brand.

snippet.title: In awe at D.C.'s Air and Space Museum
snippet.description: Road Trip 2010: No visit to the nation's capital would be complete for any self-respecting geek without a chance to see some of the most important air and spacecraft in history.

snippet.title: 10 spookiest items at the National Museum of American History (pictures)
snippet.description: The National Museum of American History is digging into the archives and unearthing a few of its favorite creepy finds.

snippet.title: 7-foot-tall hedgehog piques 'Natural Curiosities'
snippet.description: A giant hedgehog statue is spotted in London's Clapham Common after a survey reveals many Brits have never seen one in the wild. Naturalist Sir David Attenborough hopes to educate the masses about such creatures on his new show.

snippet.title: The long, great history of zeppelins
snippet.description: Road Trip 2011: The last one was decommissioned in 1940, but there was a day when Germany's zeppelins were the royalty of the skies. CNET visits the Zeppelin Museum to look at the history of aerial royalty.

snippet.title: A tour of 600 years of watchmaking history
snippet.description: Road Trip 2011: Visitors to the Patek Philippe Museum in Geneva can wander among dozens and dozens of the world's most beautiful watches. But the collection also features an archive of beautiful timepieces dating back to the 16th century.

snippet.title: Slides, whales, and tunnels, oh my: A 'museum' like no other
snippet.description: Who can resist climbing a bus hanging off a building? CNET Road Trip 2013 visited the City Museum in St. Louis, and packed with secret tunnels and giant whales, it's unlike any other museum.
